content.description: Begin on a boulder at the left side of the Good Block. Pull through the low roof and climb past a few pockets to get to the lower angle face above. Follow this up and slightly right to the top. You must climb one of the other routes on this block in order to set this up on toprope.
content.location: Located to the left of "A Good Climb" on the left corner of the Good Block. It is accessed by taking a right down the hill towards the river before the Tilted Tree Corridor.

content.description:
Start sitting with hands in a giant pocket. Move up through a crimp and a sidepull and then traverse right through underclings to the flake (stays under the roof until the flake). Move up at the flake and finish at the horizontal about 15 feet off the ground (about 4-5 feet above the death bolt).

This route is #3 on Boulder 1: The Good Block in the Good Block Area in the Brayack and Keenan Falcon Guidebook.
content.location: On the Good Block Boulder. From the Tilted Tree Corridor head downhill and left to the largest boulder. Start is the giant pocket on the right side of the overhang. Continues right to the giant flake.

content.description: Start sitting with hands on a high pocket on the arete. Move up the arete using a crimp and a sloper to the slopey topout over the arete.
content.location: From the Good Block boulder problems turn around. You’ll be facing the face with this problem. This is the short left arete.

content.description:
Stand up on pockets at the bottom of the face  under the point of the triangle. Using a series of slopers follow the line of holds under the point and top out over the point.

This route is #7 on Boulder 3 in the Good Block Area in the Brayack and Keenan Falcon Guidebook.
content.location: On the triangular boulder about 30 feet down the hill from the main trail as it goes by the Tilted Tree Corridor. This tall route is under the point of the triangle

content.description: Sit start on the right arête with a left hand in a large pocket and right hand pinching the arête. Find feet (maybe a heelhook) and move up the arête using slopers, a sidepull, and some pockets until you can move through the dihedral. From the dihedral, climb up easier slab using slopers and jugs on the arête. Climbers with larger feet may find not dabbing on the rock at the sit start to be difficult.
content.protection: A pad for the sit start and a pad for the highball slab topout, or a spotter to move pads.
content.location: On the triangular boulder about 30 feet down the hill from the main trail as it goes by the Tilted Tree Corridor. This climb goes up the right arête with feet on the dihedral.

content.description: Climb the low angle slab past a few horizontal cracks and pockets to the top. This climb has a few tricky moves.
content.protection: Small/medium sized cams, one bolt, bolted anchor
content.location: Located just to the right of "A Very Good Climb" on the right side of the Good Block. It is accessed by taking a right down the hill towards the river before the Tilted Tree Corridor.

content.description:
Start sitting using a sloper for hands. Find some feet (Difficulty seems dependent on the feet you use). Move up and slightly right to a right facing sloper and top out over the sloping arete.

This route is #6 on Boulder 3 in the Good Block Area in the Brayack and Keenan Falcon Guidebook
content.location: On the triangular boulder about 30 feet down the hill from the main trail as it goes by the Tilted Tree Corridor. This short route is on the left side of the face about 6 feet right of the left arete. Starts on a noticeable sloper.

content.description: Climb the tall, delicate slab just to the right of Shadow Boxer.
content.location: The Slab just to the right of Shadow Boxer.

content.description: A classic Coopers Rock power problem. Sit start using the sloping arete and power through the steep, overhanging face to the easy slab above.
content.location: Located in a small cave past the Tilted Tree Corridor and just before Pump It Out.

content.description: Sit start matched on the grippy slopping sidepull with wide feet. Pull up to a nice gritty crimp rail and climb up through easier slab, trending left through slopers, a mono pocket, and jugs while avoiding the arête.
content.protection: A pad for the highball top and a pad for your gouch,
content.location: On the triangular boulder about 30 feet down the hill from the main trail as it goes by the Tilted Tree Corridor. Right of Triangle Slab, you might find a small stump of an old tree, the sit start is just right of the stump.

content.description: Short, but with fun, core intensive movement. Start on knobby jug rail to move up and left. Pedestal to the left is on.
content.location: Right of shadow boxer. On the opposite the same boulder where "Epstein Didn't Kill Himself" is located

content.description: Start sitting with hands in the large horizontal. Make a loooooong deadpoint move to a sloping ledge. Move straight up through a couple incut crimps to the top. Find the big top out jug and finish.
content.location: From the Good Block Boulder problems turn around. This route is in the middle of the river face of the boulder slightly uphill.

content.description: A classic Cal Swoager gritstone route! Make a few surprisingly difficult moves to get off the ground and into the cracks, follow these to a good two finger pocket. From the pocket, make a huge dynamic move to a jug, and then another big move to the top. This route may be short, but it is steep and packs a serious punch! A fun toprope but a serious lead.
content.protection: Two anchor bolts for toproping or a few small cams, nuts, and crash pads if going for the lead.
content.location: Follow the trail past the Tilted Tree Corridor and over a few large boulders. Either go through or around the small cave that contains Shadow Boxer. Pump It Out is on the face just behind it.

content.description: Sit start on the little shelf below the left facing flake. Move up through the suspect flake, then transition up and over the lip through a good hold and continue up to the top out. Don’t use the flake above the suspect flake. It is even more sus and will probably break.
content.location: On the sideways boulder wedged between the Shadow Boxer boulder and the larger boulder to the right of it (looking downhill). This is on the riverside face.

content.description:
Start standing on the right side of the face using a sloping rail for hands. Make your way left to the same jug as Bouldem Probler (between the crack and the starting hold of this problem) and top out straight up. Guidebook recommends heel hooking the start hold for style points. Avoids the arete.

This route is #4b on Boulder 2 in the Good Block Area in the Brayack and Keenan Falcon Guidebook
content.location: From the Tilted Tree Corridor (Rubik's Cube problem) turn around and go down the hill to the short boulder nearest you. This boulder is to the right of the boulder that has the giant tree fallen beside it. This starts on the sloper rail just left of the right arete.

content.description: Start sitting with a large ledge for hands. Move left to a big pocket/sidepull and then straight up for the heel hook topout.
content.location: Look for the large featured pocket that is in the middle of the big horizontal ledge. Route is right of middle on the face.

content.description: Start sitting with hands on a good horizontal. Move up through a sloping pocket to the sloping topout.
content.location: This route is ~4 feet left of the right arete.

content.description: Stand start and follow the loose and dirty left-facing flake to a top out by the small tree
content.location: In the small corridor by Shadow Boxer

content.description:
Start on a slopey jug and crimp on the left side of the roof (you’ll be sitting on a rock). Follow jugs to the arete. Move up the arete through a horizontal to a crimp and a hidden jug. Move back left for the finish matching on slopey horizontal below the triangular prow.

This route is #1 on Boulder 1: The Good Block in the Good Block Area in the Brayack and Keenan Falcon Guidebook.
content.protection: Bring pads and a couple spotters. You have to jump down and it’s a really bad landing.
content.location: From the Tilted Tree Corridor head downhill and left to the largest boulder. This roof is riverside (and facing downhill on the left side). This is the furthest downhill route under the roof.

content.description: Dyno variation of One-Eyed. Dyno from the start hold directly to the top. Top out the same.
content.location: Look for the large featured pocket that is in the middle of the big horizontal ledge. Route is right of middle on the face.

content.description: Begin  on the lip with feet beneath the overhang. Climb out utilizing the line of crimps.
content.location: Small block to the right of Shadow Boxer. On side facing trail

content.description:
Start standing using the distinguished crack in the middle of the face for hands. Establish feet (guidebook says it’s a hop but you can get a high foot and it’s a much cooler move at the same grade and in this climbers opinion much more official) and make a long move up and left to the lowered lip and top out straight up from there.

This route is #4 on Boulder 2 in the Good Block Area in the Brayack and Keenan Falcon Guidebook.
content.location: From the Tilted Tree Corridor (Rubik's Cube problem) turn around and go down the hill to the short boulder nearest you. This boulder is to the right of the boulder that has the giant tree fallen beside it. This short problem follows the crack in the middle of the face.

content.description:
Start standing using the distinguished crack in the middle of the face for hands. You start lower on the crack than the previous problem. Establish feet far right (guidebook says it’s a hop but using this foot it’s a much cooler move at the same grade and in this climbers opinion much more official). Orient your body and make a hop move up and right  to the noticeable jug and top out straight up from there.

This route is #4a on Boulder 2 in the Good Block Area in the Brayack and Keenan Falcon Guidebook.
content.location: From the Tilted Tree Corridor (Rubik's Cube problem) turn around and go down the hill to the short boulder nearest you. This boulder is to the right of the boulder that has the giant tree fallen beside it. This short problem starts on the crack in the middle of the face.

content.description: Climb a low right-facing corner to a horizontal crack. Continue climbing straight up using small, sloping holds past three bolts to the top.
content.protection: A small/medium cam or two for the horizontal crack, three bolts, bolted anchor
content.location: Located just to the right of "A Good Climb" on the Good Block. It is accessed by taking a right down the hill towards the river before the Tilted Tree Corridor.

content.description: Climb a low right-facing corner to a horizontal crack. Follow the crack to the left and up onto the face past a single bolt. Continue moving up and left to a left-facing flake that takes you to the top.
content.protection: Standard rack, one bolt, bolted anchor
content.location: Located just to the left of "A Very Good Climb" on the Good Block. It is accessed by taking a right down the hill towards the river before the Tilted Tree Corridor.
